# pikiloom-skills — shared local secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to  ~/.pikiloom/skills.env  and fill in only the keys you need.
#
#   cp .env.example ~/.pikiloom/skills.env && chmod 600 ~/.pikiloom/skills.env
#
# Every skill resolves a key in this order (first hit wins):
#   CLI flag  →  process env  →  skill-specific *_ENV_FILE  →  ~/.pikiloom/skills.env
#
# NEVER commit the filled-in file. The repo's .gitignore drops *.env on purpose.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── image-gen ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use a DIRECT OpenAI key (sk-... / sk-svcacct-...), NOT an OpenRouter key:
# image-gen calls OpenAI's native Images API (/v1/images/*), which OpenRouter
# doesn't expose (it does image generation via /chat/completions image output).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the OpenAI-compatible base URL (proxy / gateway).
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# ── video-use ── voiceover TTS (OPTIONAL — subtitles need zero keys) ──────────
# OpenRouter key for gpt-audio voiceover; without it use `--engine say` (macOS).
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# Optional login for the page-tour recorder (keeps creds out of `ps`):
# RECORD_WEB_EMAIL=
# RECORD_WEB_PASSWORD=
# Optional, ONLY for word-level editing of spoken-source footage (upstream tool):
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# ── tech-intel ── embeddable signal pipeline ───────────────────────────────────
# LLM draft step reuses OPENROUTER_API_KEY above.
# Feishu publisher (`run.py --feishu`): creates a doc + DMs a card. The app needs
# the `docx:document` and `im:message:send_as_bot` scopes; RECEIVE_ID is your open_id.
# NOTE: these three resolve skills.env-FIRST (unlike other keys, which are env-first).
# A pikiloom host injects its own bot's FEISHU_APP_ID/SECRET into the process env;
# that bot is a different app (other open_id space, no docx scope), so the
# content-publishing app below must win. Per-run override: TECH_INTEL_FEISHU_*.
FEISHU_APP_ID=
FEISHU_APP_SECRET=
FEISHU_RECEIVE_ID=
